Program: Last Word
Title: Wallace Cunningham, Lord Gould, Alfonso Cano and Joe Frazier
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b016x4tc
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 13 Nov 2011
Matthew Bannister on The Battle of Britain pilot Wallace Cunnigham, who took part in the celebrated "Wooden Horse" escape from a German prisoner of war camp. Lord Gould - the political strategist behind New Labour. Lord Mandelson and Alastair Campbell pay tribute. Alfonso Cano - communist leader of the FARC militants in Columbia And heavyweight boxer Joe Frazier - we recall the Thriller in Manila and have a tribute from the philosopher AC Grayling. Show less